Treasury Secretary James Bakerexpressed doubts about a proposal to tax securitiestransactions as a solution to the budget deficit and said itcould hurt financial markets.    "If you start taxing markets, it could impair theirefficiency," Baker said after a speech to the National NewspaperAssociation.    "The problem is not that Americans are undertaxed. We as agovernment are overspending," he told reporters.    House Speaker Jim Wright (D-Tex) has proposed a transfertax to be paid by buyers and sellers of stocks. Reuter&#3;